    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <head>No. 217.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Washburne</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 9, 1873</date>.
                            (Received September 26.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 851.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch “separate” of July
                        2, I have the honor to inclose the translation of a dispatch received from
                        the Due de Broglie upon the subject of the coinage of the mint in France,
                        together with a tabular statement of the coinage for the years 1871 and
                        1872.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. B. WASHBURNE.</signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0497" n="401" xml:id="pg_401"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Duc <persName type="from">de Broglie</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Washburne</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Versailles</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-09-08">
                                <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 8,
                                    1873</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In the letter which you did me the honor
                            to write me on the 15th July last, you expressed the wish to receive two
                            copies of the last annual report on the manufacture of coin in
                            France.</p>
                    <p>The minister of the finances, to whom I hastened to apply for these
                            documents, has replied to me that they are not published separately, and
                            that they form part of the general statement of the administration of
                            the finances under the title of “Compte du service des monnaies,”
                            comprising, in addition to detailed statements of all the operations of
                            the mints, a recapitulation of the coin struck up to the 31st of
                            December of each year.</p>
                    <p>However, as the last printed report is that for the year 1870, Mr. Magne
                            has thought it well to send me, in reply to your request, the statement
                            of the coinage of 1871 and 1872.</p>
                    <p>I have the honor, sir, to transmit them to you herewith.</p>
                    <p>Receive, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>DE BROGLIE.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
